03850nam a22006255i 9780292797895DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20212003txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927978957 a10.7560/7346542doi  a(DE-B1597)588393  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 4aF387b.H355 2003 7aHIS0360102bisacsh04a929/.5/0257641 aHarvey, Bill, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTexas Cemeteries :bThe Resting Places of Famous, Infamous, and Just Plain Interesting Texans /cBill Harvey. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2021] 4c©2003  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tLocating the Cemetery and Gravesite You Are Seeking -- tShooting Stones—Taking Great Photos in a Cemetery -- tAround the State -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFrom the simplest slab of weathered stone to the most imposing mausoleum, every marker in a Texas cemetery bears witness to a life that—in ways small or large—helped shape the history and culture of the state. Telling the stories of some of these significant lives is the purpose of this book. Within its pages, you'll meet not only the heroes of the Texas Revolution, for example, but also one of the great African American cowboys of the traildriving era (Bose Ikard) and the first woman in Texas elected to statewide office (Annie Webb Blanton). Visiting cemeteries from every era and all regions of the state, Bill Harvey recounts the histories of famous, infamous, and just plain interesting Texans who lie at rest in Texas cemeteries. The book is organized alphabetically by city for easy reference. For each city, Harvey lists one or more cemeteries, giving their location and history, if significant. At the heart of the book are his profiles of the noteworthy people buried in each cemetery. They include not only famous but also lesser-known and even unknown Texans who made important contributions to the state in the arts, sports, business, military service, politics—truly every area of communal life. For those who want to visit these resting places, Harvey also includes tips on finding cemeteries, locating gravesites, and taking good photographs. Spend time with him in the graveyards of Texas, and you'll soon appreciate what fascinating stories the silent stones can tell.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCemeterieszTexasvDirectories. 0aCemeterieszTexasxHistory. 0aPhotographyzTexasvAmateurs' manuals. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292797895423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292797895/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK